te / we had to take a voucher to McDonalds if we wanted to fulfil their commitment to provide a &quot;continental breakfast&quot; so therefore if you are good with egg and bacon sandwiches and terrible coffee every morning you will love it / theTV remote didnt work and no one could figure it out for us so if we wanted to change the TV channel we had to climb over our suitcases to do so / no closet to hang anything up in / no iron or board to press your cloths that you couldnt hang up.....you get the picture. If your a single person and simply want a place to lay your head for the night, dont mind being dissapointed and cheated a little bit, you might like the Boulevard/Easy Hotel. Otherwise, spend the extra 25--50 pounds a night and get a real hotel. There are 100 within a mile of Paddington. Now we know and wont make the same mistake twice.	
