May 30 2006	Duck into the Boulevard	I had done a fair amount of online research in advance of my one-night stop over in London and was glad to have discovered the Boulevard. My criteria: a low-priced, reasonably comfortable lodging in close proximity to Paddington Station (and the Heathrow Express). I am happy to report that the Boulevard hit all the right notes. My 3rd floor single was just 50 pounds for the night (booked about 5 weeks in advance online) and it met all of my needs very nicely. Yes, the bedroom was quite small and the en suite bathroom was closet-like, but the spaces were well-designed and tastefully decorated. I slept okay, despite some moderate street noise (ear plugs recommended if you're a light sleeper like me). The room did not have any instructions regarding a wake-up call nor was there an alarm clock, so I set the alarm on my cell phone and that sufficed. Good thing, since I needed to catch a 5:30am-ish Express train to LHR. This was easily accomplished since the hotel is just 5 minutes walk from Paddington Station (from the right front entrance of the station, walk straight ahead to either platform 6 or 7; the Express ticket kiosk is right there and the trains leave every 20 minutes to Heathrow from 5:10am on). The neighborhood was decent and had I stayed in town any longer, I'd have likely explored the tree-lined residential area surrounding the hotel and the shops and food options nearby on Praed St. In summary, the Boulevard was ideal for one night, especially given that I was a solo guest, traveling light. Recommended!	
