May 27 2004	Tiny but nothing a little coordination can't handle	It took us about an hour to find the hotel (which is a 5-minute walk from Paddington) oops. Tired &amp; grumpy from our long flight, we were ecstatic to finally find the hotel (turn left once you get out of Paddington Station &amp; it's on the second street on the right). Unfortunately, they wouldn't let us check in until 2 but they did hold our luggage while we got some lunch. Since there are no lifts, the two of us (girls), who packed enough for 3 wks for our 1 wk stay, struggled with our luggage up the steep &amp; tiny stairs (PIVOT). Our battle up the stairs was humorous enough, but the room was even funnier. Seriously, 15x7 at best. I could lay across the bed &amp; touch both walls. We did have a room at the front of the building, which was loud, but helped us get up in the morning to go sightseeing after those long nights in London. The bathroom is the tinniest thing ever. While washing your hair, you are almost guaranteed bruised elbows and washing your face takes mad coordination skills. Somehow, we were able to contort ourselves around the room throughout the week. Breakfast was pretty much coffee and toast. This hotel was definitely a part of our &quot;London Experience&quot; clean, cheap &amp; memorable. Who could ask for more?	
Apr 28 2004	Cheap and moderately comfortable.	The Boulevard is conveniently located two blocks from the Paddington rail and tube stations. The rooms are very small, and the en suite bathrooms even smaller. It is bare-bones, but the price can't be beat in London. The breakfast of corn flakes, coffee, and toast was uninspired, but filled the void and saved the cost of an extra meal in very expensive London.	
Apr 28 2004	Compact Clean and a bargain!	Great value for your money.I stayed in a single at the Boulevard Hotel last week for four nights. Considering what a hotel in London costs getting a really up to date, albeit QUITE small room, in central London is great. Situated a short walk from the Paddington Underground station, I had no trouble getting anywhere I wanted in the city.The room itself was clean and small. My room was located on the interior, with my window facing a sort of tiny courtyard. It let in light with no view, but I also didn't notice any of the traffic noise others have mentioned. If you're planning to spend a lot of time in your hotel room, it might be a little claustraphobic. However, if, like me, you intend to spend most of your trip exploring the city, it's perfect.I can't comment on breakfast as I was out each morning before breakfast was served. The hotel staff was courteous and helpful when I asked, for example, for wake-up calls. Would stay there again.	
Apr 26 2004	Cheap clean and well located	Boulevard hotel is a real bargain for London: cheap, clean and well located near Paddington and the tube (4 lines).We booked a small double room for 2. Of course, it is rather small but not smaller than my student room (so I am used to it). There's a bed with a shelf above it, a small table, a cupboard, a drawer and a desk with a stool. It's great to have one's own bathroom, even if it is small. The breakfast was perfect for us and the staff very friendly. The room was cleaned everyday.The only problem was the noise from the street. Rooms at the front are just in front of a very busy bus stop and the noise can really be annoying during the night.Something to know: there are three floors without lift!	
